        "content": "<p><strong>Damascus steel patterns</strong>: understand how 67-layer construction creates the distinctive flowing pattern and what it means for blade performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/damascus-pattern-performance-price-guide\">Damascus pattern guide</a></p><p>Keep your Yu Series blades looking their best with our complete <strong>Damascus care guide</strong> — cleaning, drying, and long-term storage tips. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-care-for-damascus-steel-knives\">Damascus care guide</a></p><p>What’s the real difference between <strong>67-layer and 73-layer Damascus</strong>? Our guide breaks down layer count, steel composition, and performance. <a href=\"/blogs/news/67-layer-vs-73-layer-damascus\">67 vs 73 layer Damascus</a></p><p>Read our comprehensive <strong>Xinzuo brand review</strong> covering quality, materials, warranty, and how the Yu Series fits into the wider range. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-review-brand-guide\">Xinzuo brand review</a></p><p>Want a more distinctive aesthetic? The <strong>Mo Series</strong> features the same Damascus steel with striking burnt oak Shou Sugi Ban handles. <a href=\"/collections/xinzuo-mo-series-knives\">Shop the Mo Series</a></p><p>Compare all Xinzuo and Hezhen knife series side by side — steel, hardness, handles, and pricing. <a href=\"/blogs/news/xinzuo-knives-series-comparison-guide\">Full series comparison guide</a></p>",
